post_text:
Students in English language arts teacher Jeanette Cole’s world mythology class have been studying pop culture mythology, particularly how mythology lives on in our current society. Recently, they explored runes, which are letters or symbols belonging to a written language.

For example, JRR Tolkien, famous Lord of the Rings author, explored the use of runes in many of his novels, forming his own language. The Bluetooth symbol is a combination of two runes from the younger futhark, which was the runic alphabet that the Vikings used in the Viking age. They used the initials of Harald Bluetooth, to create what is called a bindrune, by merging his two initials together.

At the end of the lesson, students were asked to create their own rune. Student Sierra Omerzo’s submitted this!

Tumblebooks is offering free access to their resources until August 31, 2020. TumbleBooks’ databases are easy to use, and feature unlimited access from home! Your students can read as many books as they want, when they want, and on any device. There are no check-outs, holds, or bulky downloads.

Books are available instantly.

Tumble Book Library: https://www.tumblebooklibrary.com/auto_login.aspx?U=tumble735&P=books

Tumble Math: https://www.tumblemath.com/autologin.aspx?U=tumble2020&P=A3b5c6

Teen Book Cloud: https://www.teenbookcloud.com/autologin.aspx?U=tumble2020&P=A3b5c6

Audio Book Cloud: https://www.audiobookcloud.com/autologin.aspx?U=tumble2020&P=A3b5c6

As always you can find our list of educational and community resources here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1n2sPRTP7CW6Ugrh9bwSf_M1YGGbgd7GoysUFmZfpgLs/edit?usp=sharing

In case you missed it, Ohio lawmakers voted on Wednesday, March 25, 2020, to NOT rescheduled the primary election, which means Ohioans who wish to vote and haven't done so already will have to complete mail-in absentee ballots.

According to the Trumbull County Board of Elections, "ABSENTEE VOTING FOR THE PRIMARY ELECTION HAS BEEN EXTENDED THROUGH APRIL 28, 2020. THERE WILL BE NO IN-PERSON VOTING, ALL VOTING SHALL TAKE PLACE THROUGH THE MAIL. YOU CAN OBTAIN AN APPLICATION FOR ABSENTEE VOTING BY CLICKING THE LINK ON OUR HOMEPAGE OR BY CALLING OUR OFFICE AND REQUESTING ONE. YOU MUST COMPLETE AN ABSENTEE APPLICATION (INCLUDING PARTY SELECTION) AND RETURN THE ORIGINAL APPLICATION TO THE BOARD OF ELECTIONS BY APRIL 25th."

Trumbull County Board of Elections: https://www.boe.co.trumbull.oh.us/

Absentee Ballot Application: https://www.boe.co.trumbull.oh.us/pdfs/Absentee%20Application.pdf

post_text:
The COVID-19 virus situation is changing rapidly in the State of Ohio. While there have been no confirmed cases of COVID-19 among Mathews students or staff, we are taking preventative measures and will close the school district Friday, March 13, 2020 and Monday, March 16, 2020 Additionally, Governor DeWine has ordered schools closed for a period of three weeks beginning Tuesday, March 17, 2020.

Effective Friday, March 13, 2020, all activities including athletic practices and games are cancelled until further notice. There will be no extra-curricular activities during the school closure and there will be absolutely no exceptions to this directive. School properties will be completely closed…

shared_text:
Mustangs Care
March 5 at 12:54 PM ·

Friends of Mustangs Care! Our food donations have been down this winter. We have 13 weeks left of back pack meals this school year. We are currently serving 57 students at Mathews.

We were wondering if anyone wouldn’t mind picking up a few extra items for us next time you go grocery shopping?

We’ve compiled an ALDI and Sam’s Club price list of our most needed items right now. If you shop either of these stores, please take a look and see if you could donate these items!

Donations can be dropped off in our donation box at Cortland Bank - Vienna Branch (4434 Warren Sharon Rd) or message us for alternate drop off arrangements.

Please comment below if you plan on helping us out! Like and Share to spread the word!
Thank you so much!! ❤️🖤

post_text:
KINDERGARTEN REGISTRATION!!

The Mathews Local School District will hold its kindergarten registration at Currie Elementary through March 6, 2020, from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m.

Your child must be 5 by August 1, 2020. Please bring your child’s birth certificate, immunization record, social security card, proof of residency and driver’s license to registration. If there has been a separation or divorce, please bring proof of legal custody. You do not need to bring your child to the school to register him or her.

The district will host its kindergarten screenings in the spring. More information will be released at registration.
